text: The bank has one, non-metropolitan assessment area (AA).  The AA consists of 12 whole
label: BODY

text: counties (Benson, Bottineau, Dunn, Eddy, Foster, McHenry, McLean, Pierce, Ramsey, Stark,
label: BODY

text: Stutsman, and Ward).  The AA resembles an upside down “U” covering the north central part of
label: BODY

text: the state.  Although the AA is primarily comprised of middle- and upper-income geographies, it
label: BODY

text: does contain seven moderate-income areas.  The moderate-income geographies are spread
label: BODY

text: throughout the AA.  The AA does not contain any low-income geographies.  The AA complies
label: BODY

text: with regulatory guidelines and does not arbitrarily exclude LMI areas.
label: BODY

text: The economy is stable and has a mixture of agriculture, manufacturing, and service industries.
label: BODY

text: The economy is heavily dependent on agriculture as many of the businesses are directly related to
label: BODY

text: agriculture.  Major agricultural products include wheat, barley, sunflowers, and beef cattle.
label: BODY

text: Unemployment is well below the national average.
label: BODY

text: We performed a community contact with an economic development organization.  We also
label: BODY

text: reviewed five recent contacts by other regulators with tribal government, local government, and
label: BODY

text: economic development representatives.  Contacts cited a credit need for business start up and
label: BODY

text: expansion loans.  They indicated that area banks are very active in the community and are
label: BODY

text: generally meeting area credit needs.  Some contacts indicated a need for housing stock in some
label: BODY

text: communities, while other communities had ample housing.
label: BODY

text: Community development opportunities in the assessment area are somewhat limited.  We did not
label: BODY

text: identify any significant opportunities for community development loans, investments or services
label: BODY

text: in our performance context research, community contact work, or our review of the CRA
label: BODY

text: performance evaluations of competing banks.  As evidenced by the bank’s performance,
label: BODY

text: community development opportunities primarily consist of loans, contributions, and service work
label: BODY

text: with nonprofit organizations that have a community development purpose.
label: BODY

text: Numerous commercial banks provide strong competition for bank services in the AA.  Bremer
label: BODY

text: has the largest deposit market share in the AA (13%) as of June 30, 2001.  Institutions with the
label: BODY

text: next highest market shares are significantly larger institutions that serve much larger geographic
label: BODY

text: areas - Wells Fargo Bank North Dakota, N.A. (12%) and U.S. Bank N.A. (8%).  Other
label: BODY

text: competitors have less than an 8% deposit market share each and primarily consist of small,
